HEADWORD: Orcein
<hw>Or"ce*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
reddish brown amorphous dyestuff, <chform>C7H7NO3</chform>, obtained
from orcin, and forming the essential coloring matter of cudbear and
archil. It is closely related to litmus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

